From d29bcafeccf7da86920cb151f808d52da6bf8ec4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ganesh Kariganuru Mahabalesh <gkarigan@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 19 Jun 2025 15:02:32 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:DP:wifi:ath12k:modularize NSS plugin interface 
for ath12k and PPE modules

Introduce qca-wifi-nss-plugin and qca-nss-wifi-plugin modules to decouple 
symbol dependencies between ath12k and PPE components.

- Register and unregister NSS plugin ops to isolate ath12k from 
  direct PPE symbol usage.
- Delegate VP number allocation and deallocation to ath_client; 
  ath12k retrieves the assigned VP number via get_vp_num op 
  from nss-wifi-plugin.
- Move DS resource management (alloc/dealloc/start/stop),
  VP config updates, and service status updates to nss-wifi-plugin.
- Remove PPEDS handle; update all ppeds_wlan_ops to use ppeds_node_id 
  instead of wlan_handle. 
  Implement ppeds_node_id-to-SoC mapping using ds_node_map.
- Export ppe_fse_ops and ppe_ds_wlan_ops to allow direct invocation 
  from wifi-nss-plugin.

Patch-dependency:
	0337-01-QSDK-DP-wifi-Add-support-for-PPE-DS-Direct-switch-fe.patch

Signed-off-by: Ganesh Kariganuru Mahabalesh <gkarigan@qti.qualcomm.com>
